# Contributing

Thank you for your contribution. Please follow these steps to contribute.

## Pull Request Process

1. Fork the repository ([How to](https://help.github.com/en/articles/fork-a-repo))
1. Clone the repository ([How to](https://help.github.com/en/articles/cloning-a-repository))
1. Create a feature branch (anything but master) from origin/master, ([How to](https://help.github.com/en/articles/creating-and-deleting-branches-within-your-repository))
1. Make your changes locally
1. Test your changes locally!
1. Update the README.md with details of changes to the interface, this includes new environment variables, exposed ports, useful file locations and container parameters.
1. Commit your changes ([How to](https://help.github.com/en/desktop/contributing-to-projects/committing-and-reviewing-changes-to-your-project))
1. Push to GHE ([How to](https://help.github.com/en/articles/pushing-to-a-remote))
   * [Create](https://github.concur.com/talos/criteria/compare) a Pull Request ([How to](https://help.github.com/en/articles/creating-a-pull-request))
   * Follow the instructions in the [PR template](PULL_REQUEST_TEMPLATE.md) and describe your requested change
1. Make sure all checks pass ([How to](https://help.github.com/en/articles/about-required-status-checks))
1. Get it reviewed in a timely manner ([How to](https://help.github.com/en/articles/about-pull-request-reviews))
   * It is **your** responsibility to follow up with reviewers
   * Additional commits will invalidate prior approvals
   * Complete requested changes in a timely manner
   * Rebase your changes onto master if your branch goes stale ([more info](https://github.com/servo/servo/wiki/Beginner's-guide-to-rebasing-and-squashing))
1. Have a user with permissions accept the pull request ([squash and merge](https://help.github.com/en/articles/merging-a-pull-request))
1. Delete the feature branch ([deleting branches in pull request](https://help.github.com/en/articles/deleting-and-restoring-branches-in-a-pull-request))

That's it! Get forking!

[![GitHub Flow](/images/forking-flow.png)](https://help.github.com/en/articles/forking-flow)
